<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1658,2045]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Asexual stage fusarium-like. Conidiophores arising directly from somatic hyphae, simple or rarely branched, monochasial, straight, hyaline, smooth-walled, aseptate or with basal septum, up to 42 µm long. Conidiogenous cells monophialidic or rarely polyphialidic, arising laterally from hyphae or in terminal pairs, cylindrical to subulate, 8−14 × 1.5−3 µm, thin- and smooth-walled. On PDA, macroconidia falcate, long fusiform, slightly narrowing towards the ends, acute, the apical cell often hooked with a more or less pointed tip, basal cell slightly pedicellate, hyaline, thin-and smooth-walled, (1−)3(−4)-septate, (25−)36−42(−53) × 2.5−3.5 µm (av. 39.5 × 2.8 µm) (n = 30), microconidia slightly curved to C-shaped, hyaline, smooth, aseptate, 11–18(−22) × 0.85–1.3 µm (av. 15.7 × 1.1 µm) (n = 20). On OA, macroconidia falcate, generally crescent to threadlike, (3–)4–9-septate, (32−)40–65(−80) × 2.3–3.8 µm (av. 53.2 × 2.9 µm) (n = 30), microconidia strongly curved, hyaline, smooth, 0−4(−5)-septate, (12−)15–24(−32) × 0.85–1.4(−2.2) µm (av. 19.3 × 1.2 µm) (n = 30).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1658,2045]" box="[189,489,2018,2045]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Sexual stage not observed.</paragraph>
